{"version":"https://jsonfeed.org/version/1.1","title":"Web - Category | ꜱᴘᴀᴡɴ𝟐ᴘᴡɴ","description":"Personal CTF writeups and cybersecurity notes.","home_page_url":"https://nfl-alvis.github.io/ctf-writeups/","language":"en","icon":"https://nfl-alvis.github.io/apple-touch-icon.png","favicon":"https://nfl-alvis.github.io/favicon.ico","authors":[{"name":"spawn2pwn","url":"https://github.com/nfl-alvis","avatar":"https://nfl-alvis.github.io/images/IdaWin.png"}],"items":[{"title":"Fools Mate","date_published":"2026-07-10T00:00:00&#43;08:00","date_modified":"2026-07-10T22:44:30&#43;07:00","id":"https://nfl-alvis.github.io/ctf-writeups/posts/fools-mate/","url":"https://nfl-alvis.github.io/ctf-writeups/posts/fools-mate/","authors":[{"name":"spawn2pwn","url":"https://github.com/nfl-alvis","avatar":"https://gravatar.loli.net/avatar/b01c9af4b33ead25b072a03f8d0c5508?s=32&amp;d=mp"}],"tags":["Insecure Client-Side Controls"],"summary":" Can you bypass the engine?\nTL;DR Fool’s Mate is an easy TryHackMe web challenge that demonstrates why client-side security controls cannot be trusted. Although the application prevents a winning chess move in the browser, the backend API still accepts the request when it is modified and sent manually through Burp Suite. Initial Analysis The target is a web-based chess endgame trainer. When opening the application, we are presented with a chessboard and instructed to deliver checkmate in one move.\n","content_html":"\u003ca class=\"lightgallery\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"/ctf-writeups/posts/fools-mate/images/room_image.webp\" title=\"/ctf-writeups/posts/fools-mate/images/room_image.webp\" data-thumbnail=\"/ctf-writeups/posts/fools-mate/images/room_image.webp\" data-sub-html=\"\u003ch2\u003e/ctf-writeups/posts/fools-mate/images/room_image.webp\u003c/h2\u003e\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" src='/ctf-writeups/posts/fools-mate/images/room_image.webp' alt=\"/ctf-writeups/posts/fools-mate/images/room_image.webp\" height=\"1800\" width=\"3600\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCan you bypass the engine?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"details admonition abstract open\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv class=\"details-summary admonition-title\"\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon fa-solid fa-clipboard-list\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003eTL;DR\u003ci class=\"details-icon fa-solid fa-angle-right\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"details-content\"\u003e\n      \u003cdiv class=\"admonition-content\"\u003eFool’s Mate is an easy TryHackMe web challenge that demonstrates why client-side security controls cannot be trusted. Although the application prevents a winning chess move in the browser, the backend API still accepts the request when it is modified and sent manually through Burp Suite.\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 class=\"heading-element\" id=\"initial-analysis\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eInitial Analysis\u003c/span\u003e\n  \u003ca href=\"#initial-analysis\" class=\"heading-mark\"\u003e\n    \u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n  \u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe target is a web-based chess endgame trainer. When opening the application, we are presented with a chessboard and instructed to deliver checkmate in one move.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Neighbour","date_published":"2026-07-08T00:00:00&#43;08:00","date_modified":"2026-07-10T22:44:30&#43;07:00","id":"https://nfl-alvis.github.io/ctf-writeups/posts/neighbour/","url":"https://nfl-alvis.github.io/ctf-writeups/posts/neighbour/","authors":[{"name":"spawn2pwn","url":"https://github.com/nfl-alvis","avatar":"https://gravatar.loli.net/avatar/b01c9af4b33ead25b072a03f8d0c5508?s=32&amp;d=mp"}],"tags":["IDOR"],"summary":" Check out our new cloud service, Authentication Anywhere. Can you find other users\u0026rsquo; secrets?\nTL;DR Neighbour is an easy TryHackMe room that demonstrates an Insecure Direct Object Reference (IDOR) vulnerability. The application fails to enforce authorization checks on the profile endpoint, allowing an authenticated user to access another user\u0026rsquo;s profile by modifying the user query parameter. Initial Access We are provided with a website containing a login form.\n","content_html":"\u003ca class=\"lightgallery\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"/ctf-writeups/posts/neighbour/images/room_image.webp\" title=\"/ctf-writeups/posts/neighbour/images/room_image.webp\" data-thumbnail=\"/ctf-writeups/posts/neighbour/images/room_image.webp\" data-sub-html=\"\u003ch2\u003e/ctf-writeups/posts/neighbour/images/room_image.webp\u003c/h2\u003e\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" src='/ctf-writeups/posts/neighbour/images/room_image.webp' alt=\"/ctf-writeups/posts/neighbour/images/room_image.webp\" height=\"600\" width=\"1200\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCheck out our new cloud service, Authentication Anywhere. Can you find other users\u0026rsquo; secrets?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"details admonition abstract open\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv class=\"details-summary admonition-title\"\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon fa-solid fa-clipboard-list\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003eTL;DR\u003ci class=\"details-icon fa-solid fa-angle-right\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"details-content\"\u003e\n      \u003cdiv class=\"admonition-content\"\u003eNeighbour is an easy TryHackMe room that demonstrates an \u003cstrong\u003eInsecure Direct Object Reference (IDOR)\u003c/strong\u003e vulnerability. The application fails to enforce authorization checks on the profile endpoint, allowing an authenticated user to access another user\u0026rsquo;s profile by modifying the \u003ccode\u003euser\u003c/code\u003e query parameter.\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 class=\"heading-element\" id=\"initial-access\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eInitial Access\u003c/span\u003e\n  \u003ca href=\"#initial-access\" class=\"heading-mark\"\u003e\n    \u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n  \u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eWe are provided with a website containing a login form.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Lo-Fi","date_published":"2026-07-02T00:00:00&#43;08:00","date_modified":"2026-07-10T22:44:30&#43;07:00","id":"https://nfl-alvis.github.io/ctf-writeups/posts/lo-fi/","url":"https://nfl-alvis.github.io/ctf-writeups/posts/lo-fi/","authors":[{"name":"spawn2pwn","url":"https://github.com/nfl-alvis","avatar":"https://gravatar.loli.net/avatar/b01c9af4b33ead25b072a03f8d0c5508?s=32&amp;d=mp"}],"tags":["Local File Inclusion"],"summary":" Want to hear some lo-fi beats while relaxing or studying? We\u0026rsquo;ve got you covered!\nTL;DR Lo-Fi is an easy TryHackMe room that demonstrates a Local File Inclusion (LFI) vulnerability. By exploiting the vulnerable page parameter, it is possible to read arbitrary files from the server, including /etc/passwd. Overview The target provides a web application with a simple interface.\n","content_html":"\u003ca class=\"lightgallery\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"/ctf-writeups/posts/lo-fi/images/room_image.webp\" title=\"/ctf-writeups/posts/lo-fi/images/room_image.webp\" data-thumbnail=\"/ctf-writeups/posts/lo-fi/images/room_image.webp\" data-sub-html=\"\u003ch2\u003e/ctf-writeups/posts/lo-fi/images/room_image.webp\u003c/h2\u003e\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" src='/ctf-writeups/posts/lo-fi/images/room_image.webp' alt=\"/ctf-writeups/posts/lo-fi/images/room_image.webp\" height=\"600\" width=\"1200\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWant to hear some lo-fi beats while relaxing or studying? We\u0026rsquo;ve got you covered!\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"details admonition abstract open\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv class=\"details-summary admonition-title\"\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon fa-solid fa-clipboard-list\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003eTL;DR\u003ci class=\"details-icon fa-solid fa-angle-right\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"details-content\"\u003e\n      \u003cdiv class=\"admonition-content\"\u003eLo-Fi is an easy TryHackMe room that demonstrates a Local File Inclusion (LFI) vulnerability. By exploiting the vulnerable \u003ccode\u003epage\u003c/code\u003e parameter, it is possible to read arbitrary files from the server, including \u003ccode\u003e/etc/passwd\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 class=\"heading-element\" id=\"overview\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eOverview\u003c/span\u003e\n  \u003ca href=\"#overview\" class=\"heading-mark\"\u003e\n    \u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n  \u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe target provides a web application with a simple interface.\u003c/p\u003e"}]}